### S06 — Extract .wwp codec to app/paint/paint_wwp_codec.*

The .wwp JSON paint file format is implemented three times (see guardrail #5 above).

Steps:
1. Create `app/paint/paint_wwp_codec.h` declaring:
   - `std::string buildWwpJson(TPaintCanvasView* cv)`
   - `bool saveWwpFile(const std::string& path, const std::string& json)`
   - `bool loadWwpFromString(const std::string& data, TPaintCanvasView* cv)` (new unified loader)
   - `int  parseIntAfter(const std::string& s, size_t pos, const char* key)`
   - `bool parseBoolAfter(const std::string& s, size_t pos, const char* key)`
2. Create `app/paint/paint_wwp_codec.cpp` — move canonical implementations from `paint_window.cpp`
3. In `paint_window.cpp`: replace the local implementations with `#include "paint_wwp_codec.h"`
4. In `test_pattern_app.cpp`: replace `api_paint_save`, `api_paint_load`,
   and `api_spawn_paint_with_file` parse loops with calls to the codec functions
5. Add `paint/paint_wwp_codec.cpp` to `app/CMakeLists.txt`
6. Build and verify paint save/load still works (check no compile errors)
Commit: `refactor(paint): extract .wwp codec to paint_wwp_codec.* — E012 S06`

